Description: Corroded copper alloy barbed arrow-head of rhombic cross-section, with blunt tip, nicked edges and a thick tang (broken and incomplete) of round cross-section.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 3
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (pl. xxxix, 20)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.46, p.71, fig.3, p.183, pl.25)
